Season chicken with salt and pepper, if desired. Cook chicken in oil in large skillet over medium-high heat, 5 minutes per side. Remove and set aside. Add garlic to skillet; cook 2 minutes over low heat. Add broth and tomatoes. Bring to boil. Stir in rice and return to boil. Reduce heat to low; place chicken over rice. Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in broccoli.